# Casa Bevk

Private family hub for **exactly two users** sharing one household. Calm, warm
"Sage & Linen" theme. Not a social app.

## Stack (fixed)
Next.js 16 (App Router, `src/`, `@/*`) · React 19 · Supabase (Postgres + Auth +
Realtime + RLS) · Tailwind v4 (CSS-first `@theme`, no `tailwind.config.js`) ·
shadcn/ui · Vercel · **pnpm only** (never npm/yarn — conflicting lockfile).

## Next.js 16 gotchas
APIs differ from older Next — read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before coding.
- `middleware.ts` no longer exists → `src/proxy.ts` (named export `proxy`, Node runtime).
- `cookies()` and `headers()` are **async** — always `await`.

## Supabase / auth
- Use `@supabase/ssr` with the `getAll`/`setAll` cookie API **only**. Never the
  deprecated `@supabase/auth-helpers-nextjs` or `get/set/remove`.
- Clients: `lib/supabase/client.ts` (browser), `server.ts` (async server),
  `session.ts` (proxy refresh). Authorization in `lib/auth/dal.ts` uses
  `getUser()` (never `getSession()`); **RLS is the real backstop**.
- Invite-only: public sign-up is disabled, only two pre-provisioned users. No
  `/signup` route.

## Database
Source of truth: `supabase/migrations/`. Detailed schema + RLS template + how to
apply via the Supabase MCP are in `database.mdc`. Money is `numeric(14,2)` + a
3-letter currency (never float). Every new table is household-scoped with RLS.

## Theme
"Sage & Linen" tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` (sage `#6B8E6B` on linen
`#F7F5F0`). Use shadcn components and the semantic tokens, not raw colors.

